							</div>
							Liu Xiaobo, Nobel Prize laureate and one of China's finest, died tonight in a hospital in Shenyang, Liaoning province, having never been officially released from his 11-year sentence for state subversion. He served more than seven of those years behind bars.							<a class="read-more" href="http://beijingcream.com/2017/07/liu-xiaobo-is-dead-and-the-beijing-sky-is-in-uproar/">Read more &raquo;</a>
